Date: Tue, 1 Feb 2022 16:21:04 +0100
Subject: drm/amdgpu: add some lockdep checks to the VM code
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 2d022081b333a7f15ba27607696d4a41a7a2b5f9
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
References: jsc#PED-1166 jsc#PED-1168 jsc#PED-1170 jsc#PED-1218 jsc#PED-1220 jsc#PED-1222 jsc#PED-1223 jsc#PED-1225

Whenever a bo_va structure is added or removed the VM and eventually
added BO should be locked.

Signed-off-by: Christian KÃ¶nig <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Felix Kuehling <Felix.Kuehling@amd.com>
Acked-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vm.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vm.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vm.c
index bb82d891b278..e3da9324cb77 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vm.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vm.c
@@ -2250,6 +2250,8 @@ struct amdgpu_bo_va *amdgpu_vm_bo_add(struct amdgpu_device *adev,
 {
 	struct amdgpu_bo_va *bo_va;
 
+	dma_resv_assert_held(vm->root.bo->tbo.base.resv);
+
 	bo_va = kzalloc(sizeof(struct amdgpu_bo_va), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (bo_va == NULL) {
 		return NULL;
@@ -2263,6 +2265,7 @@ struct amdgpu_bo_va *amdgpu_vm_bo_add(struct amdgpu_device *adev,
 	if (!bo)
 		return bo_va;
 
+	dma_resv_assert_held(bo->tbo.base.resv);
 	if (amdgpu_dmabuf_is_xgmi_accessible(adev, bo)) {
 		bo_va->is_xgmi = true;
 		/* Power up XGMI if it can be potentially used */
@@ -2657,7 +2660,10 @@ void amdgpu_vm_bo_rmv(struct amdgpu_device *adev,
 	struct amdgpu_vm *vm = bo_va->base.vm;
 	struct amdgpu_vm_bo_base **base;
 
+	dma_resv_assert_held(vm->root.bo->tbo.base.resv);
+
 	if (bo) {
+		dma_resv_assert_held(bo->tbo.base.resv);
 		if (bo->tbo.base.resv == vm->root.bo->tbo.base.resv)
 			vm->bulk_moveable = false;
 
